  91 def adjust_contrastv2(images, contrast_factor, name=None):
  92   r"""Adjust the contrast of one or more images.
  93 
  94   `images` is a tensor of at least 3 dimensions.  The last 3 dimensions are
  95   interpreted as `[height, width, channels]`.  The other dimensions only
  96   represent a collection of images, such as `[batch, height, width, channels].`
  97 
  98   Contrast is adjusted independently for each channel of each image.
  99 
 100   For each channel, the Op first computes the mean of the image pixels in the
 101   channel and then adjusts each component of each pixel to
 102   `(x - mean) * contrast_factor + mean`.
 103 
 104   Args:
 105     images: A `Tensor` of type `float32`. Images to adjust.  At least 3-D.
 106     contrast_factor: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 107       A float multiplier for adjusting contrast.

 291 @tf_export('image.crop_and_resize')
 292 def crop_and_resize(image, boxes, box_ind, crop_size, method="bilinear", extrapolation_value=0, name=None):
 293   r"""Extracts crops from the input image tensor and resizes them.
 294 
 295   Extracts crops from the input image tensor and resizes them using bilinear
 296   sampling or nearest neighbor sampling (possibly with aspect ratio change) to a
 297   common output size specified by `crop_size`. This is more general than the
 298   `crop_to_bounding_box` op which extracts a fixed size slice from the input image
 299   and does not allow resizing or aspect ratio change.
 300 
 301   Returns a tensor with `crops` from the input `image` at positions defined at the
 302   bounding box locations in `boxes`. The cropped boxes are all resized (with
 303   bilinear or nearest neighbor interpolation) to a fixed
 304   `size = [crop_height, crop_width]`. The result is a 4-D tensor
 305   `[num_boxes, crop_height, crop_width, depth]`. The resizing is corner aligned.
 306   In particular, if `boxes = [[0, 0, 1, 1]]`, the method will give identical
 307   results to using `tf.image.resize_bilinear()` or
 308   `tf.image.resize_nearest_neighbor()`(depends on the `method` argument) with
 309   `align_corners=True`.
 310 
 311   Args:
 312     image: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `uint8`, `uint16`, `int8`, `int16`, `int32`, `int64`, `half`, `float32`, `float64`.
 313       A 4-D tensor of shape `[batch, image_height, image_width, depth]`.
 314       Both `image_height` and `image_width` need to be positive.
 315     boxes: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 316       A 2-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes, 4]`. The `i`-th row of the tensor
 317       specifies the coordinates of a box in the `box_ind[i]` image and is specified
 318       in normalized coordinates `[y1, x1, y2, x2]`. A normalized coordinate value of
 319       `y` is mapped to the image coordinate at `y * (image_height - 1)`, so as the
 320       `[0, 1]` interval of normalized image height is mapped to
 321       `[0, image_height - 1]` in image height coordinates. We do allow `y1` > `y2`, in
 322       which case the sampled crop is an up-down flipped version of the original
 323       image. The width dimension is treated similarly. Normalized coordinates
 324       outside the `[0, 1]` range are allowed, in which case we use
 325       `extrapolation_value` to extrapolate the input image values.
 326     box_ind: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 327       A 1-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` with int32 values in `[0, batch)`.
 328       The value of `box_ind[i]` specifies the image that the `i`-th box refers to.
 329     crop_size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 330       A 1-D tensor of 2 elements, `size = [crop_height, crop_width]`. All
 331       cropped image patches are resized to this size. The aspect ratio of the image
 332       content is not preserved. Both `crop_height` and `crop_width` need to be
 333       positive.
 334     method: An optional `string` from: `"bilinear", "nearest"`. Defaults to `"bilinear"`.
 335       A string specifying the sampling method for resizing. It can be either
 336       `"bilinear"` or `"nearest"` and default to `"bilinear"`. Currently two sampling
 337       methods are supported: Bilinear and Nearest Neighbor.
 338     extrapolation_value: An optional `float`. Defaults to `0`.
 339       Value used for extrapolation, when applicable.
 340     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 341 
 342   Returns:
 343     A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 344   """
 345   _ctx = _context._context
 346   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 347     if method is None:
 348       method = "bilinear"
 349     method = _execute.make_str(method, "method")
 350     if extrapolation_value is None:
 351       extrapolation_value = 0
 352     extrapolation_value = _execute.make_float(extrapolation_value, "extrapolation_value")
 353     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 354         "CropAndResize", image=image, boxes=boxes, box_ind=box_ind,
 355         crop_size=crop_size, method=method,
 356         extrapolation_value=extrapolation_value, name=name)
 357     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 358     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 359     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"), "method", _op.get_attr("method"),
 360               "extrapolation_value", _op.get_attr("extrapolation_value"))
 361     _execute.record_gradient(
 362       "CropAndResize", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 363     _result, = _result
 364     return _result
 365 
 366   else:
 367     try:
 368       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
 369         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
 370         "CropAndResize", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, image, boxes,
 371         box_ind, crop_size, "method", method, "extrapolation_value",
 372         extrapolation_value)
 373       return _result
 374     except _core._FallbackException:
 375       return crop_and_resize_eager_fallback(
 376           image, boxes, box_ind, crop_size, method=method,
 377           extrapolation_value=extrapolation_value, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
 378     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
 379       if name is not None:
 380         message = e.message + " name: " + name
 381       else:
 382         message = e.message
 383       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

 412 def crop_and_resize_grad_boxes(grads, image, boxes, box_ind, method="bilinear", name=None):
 413   r"""Computes the gradient of the crop_and_resize op wrt the input boxes tensor.
 414 
 415   Args:

 425       `y` is mapped to the image coordinate at `y * (image_height - 1)`, so as the

 432     box_ind: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 433       A 1-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` with int32 values in `[0, batch)`.
 434       The value of `box_ind[i]` specifies the image that the `i`-th box refers to.
 435     method: An optional `string` from: `"bilinear"`. Defaults to `"bilinear"`.
 436       A string specifying the interpolation method. Only 'bilinear' is
 437       supported for now.
 438     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 439 
 440   Returns:
 441     A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 442   """

 444   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:

 448     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 449         "CropAndResizeGradBoxes", grads=grads, image=image, boxes=boxes,

 500 def crop_and_resize_grad_image(grads, boxes, box_ind, image_size, T, method="bilinear", name=None):
 501   r"""Computes the gradient of the crop_and_resize op wrt the input image tensor.
 502 
 503   Args:
 504     grads: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 505       A 4-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes, crop_height, crop_width, depth]`.
 506     boxes: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
 507       A 2-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes, 4]`. The `i`-th row of the tensor
 508       specifies the coordinates of a box in the `box_ind[i]` image and is specified
 509       in normalized coordinates `[y1, x1, y2, x2]`. A normalized coordinate value of
 510       `y` is mapped to the image coordinate at `y * (image_height - 1)`, so as the
 511       `[0, 1]` interval of normalized image height is mapped to
 512       `[0, image_height - 1] in image height coordinates. We do allow y1 > y2, in
 513       which case the sampled crop is an up-down flipped version of the original
 514       image. The width dimension is treated similarly. Normalized coordinates
 515       outside the `[0, 1]` range are allowed, in which case we use
 516       `extrapolation_value` to extrapolate the input image values.
 517     box_ind: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 518       A 1-D tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` with int32 values in `[0, batch)`.
 519       The value of `box_ind[i]` specifies the image that the `i`-th box refers to.
 520     image_size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 521       A 1-D tensor with value `[batch, image_height, image_width, depth]`
 522       containing the original image size. Both `image_height` and `image_width` need
 523       to be positive.
 524     T: A `tf.DType` from: `tf.float32, tf.half, tf.float64`.
 525     method: An optional `string` from: `"bilinear", "nearest"`. Defaults to `"bilinear"`.
 526       A string specifying the interpolation method. Only 'bilinear' is
 527       supported for now.
 528     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 529 
 530   Returns:
 531     A `Tensor` of type `T`.
 532   """
 533   _ctx = _context._context
 534   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 535     T = _execute.make_type(T, "T")
 536     if method is None:
 537       method = "bilinear"
 538     method = _execute.make_str(method, "method")
 539     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 540         "CropAndResizeGradImage", grads=grads, boxes=boxes, box_ind=box_ind,
 541         image_size=image_size, T=T, method=method, name=name)
 542     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 543     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 544     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"), "method", _op.get_attr("method"))
 545     _execute.record_gradient(
 546       "CropAndResizeGradImage", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 547     _result, = _result
 548     return _result
 549 
 550   else:
 551     try:
 552       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
 553         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
 554         "CropAndResizeGradImage", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, grads,
 555         boxes, box_ind, image_size, "T", T, "method", method)
 556       return _result
 557     except _core._FallbackException:
 558       return crop_and_resize_grad_image_eager_fallback(
 559           grads, boxes, box_ind, image_size, T=T, method=method, name=name,
 560           ctx=_ctx)
 561     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
 562       if name is not None:
 563         message = e.message + " name: " + name
 564       else:
 565         message = e.message
 566       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
 567

 593 @tf_export('image.decode_and_crop_jpeg')
 594 def decode_and_crop_jpeg(contents, crop_window, channels=0, ratio=1, fancy_upscaling=True, try_recover_truncated=False, acceptable_fraction=1, dct_method="", name=None):
 595   r"""Decode and Crop a JPEG-encoded image to a uint8 tensor.
 596 
 597   The attr `channels` indicates the desired number of color channels for the
 598   decoded image.
 599 
 600   Accepted values are:
 601 
 602   *   0: Use the number of channels in the JPEG-encoded image.
 603   *   1: output a grayscale image.
 604   *   3: output an RGB image.
 605 
 606   If needed, the JPEG-encoded image is transformed to match the requested number
 607   of color channels.
 608 
 609   The attr `ratio` allows downscaling the image by an integer factor during
 610   decoding.  Allowed values are: 1, 2, 4, and 8.  This is much faster than
 611   downscaling the image later.
 612 
 613 
 614   It is equivalent to a combination of decode and crop, but much faster by only
 615   decoding partial jpeg image.
 616 
 617   Args:
 618     contents: A `Tensor` of type `string`. 0-D.  The JPEG-encoded image.
 619     crop_window: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 620       1-D.  The crop window: [crop_y, crop_x, crop_height, crop_width].
 621     channels: An optional `int`. Defaults to `0`.
 622       Number of color channels for the decoded image.
 623     ratio: An optional `int`. Defaults to `1`. Downscaling ratio.
 624     fancy_upscaling: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
 625       If true use a slower but nicer upscaling of the
 626       chroma planes (yuv420/422 only).
 627     try_recover_truncated: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
 628       If true try to recover an image from truncated input.
 629     acceptable_fraction: An optional `float`. Defaults to `1`.
 630       The minimum required fraction of lines before a truncated
 631       input is accepted.
 632     dct_method: An optional `string`. Defaults to `""`.
 633       string specifying a hint about the algorithm used for
 634       decompression.  Defaults to "" which maps to a system-specific
 635       default.  Currently valid values are ["INTEGER_FAST",
 636       "INTEGER_ACCURATE"].  The hint may be ignored (e.g., the internal
 637       jpeg library changes to a version that does not have that specific
 638       option.)
 639     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 640 
 641   Returns:
 642     A `Tensor` of type `uint8`.
 643   """
 644   _ctx = _context._context
 645   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 646     if channels is None:
 647       channels = 0
 648     channels = _execute.make_int(channels, "channels")
 649     if ratio is None:
 650       ratio = 1
 651     ratio = _execute.make_int(ratio, "ratio")
 652     if fancy_upscaling is None:
 653       fancy_upscaling = True
 654     fancy_upscaling = _execute.make_bool(fancy_upscaling, "fancy_upscaling")
 655     if try_recover_truncated is None:
 656       try_recover_truncated = False
 657     try_recover_truncated = _execute.make_bool(try_recover_truncated, "try_recover_truncated")
 658     if acceptable_fraction is None:
 659       acceptable_fraction = 1
 660     acceptable_fraction = _execute.make_float(acceptable_fraction, "acceptable_fraction")
 661     if dct_method is None:
 662       dct_method = ""
 663     dct_method = _execute.make_str(dct_method, "dct_method")
 664     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 665         "DecodeAndCropJpeg", contents=contents, crop_window=crop_window,
 666         channels=channels, ratio=ratio, fancy_upscaling=fancy_upscaling,
 667         try_recover_truncated=try_recover_truncated,
 668         acceptable_fraction=acceptable_fraction, dct_method=dct_method,
 669         name=name)
 670     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 671     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 672     _attrs = ("channels", _op.get_attr("channels"), "ratio",
 673               _op.get_attr("ratio"), "fancy_upscaling",
 674               _op.get_attr("fancy_upscaling"), "try_recover_truncated",
 675               _op.get_attr("try_recover_truncated"), "acceptable_fraction",
 676               _op.get_attr("acceptable_fraction"), "dct_method",
 677               _op.get_attr("dct_method"))
 678     _execute.record_gradient(
 679       "DecodeAndCropJpeg", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 680     _result, = _result
 681     return _result
 682 
 683   else:
 684     try:
 685       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
 686         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
 687         "DecodeAndCropJpeg", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, contents,
 688         crop_window, "channels", channels, "ratio", ratio, "fancy_upscaling",
 689         fancy_upscaling, "try_recover_truncated", try_recover_truncated,
 690         "acceptable_fraction", acceptable_fraction, "dct_method", dct_method)
 691       return _result
 692     except _core._FallbackException:
 693       return decode_and_crop_jpeg_eager_fallback(
 694           contents, crop_window, channels=channels, ratio=ratio,
 695           fancy_upscaling=fancy_upscaling,
 696           try_recover_truncated=try_recover_truncated,
 697           acceptable_fraction=acceptable_fraction, dct_method=dct_method,
 698           name=name, ctx=_ctx)
 699     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
 700       if name is not None:
 701         message = e.message + " name: " + name
 702       else:
 703         message = e.message
 704       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

1192 @tf_export('image.encode_jpeg')
1193 def encode_jpeg(image, format="", quality=95, progressive=False, optimize_size=False, chroma_downsampling=True, density_unit="in", x_density=300, y_density=300, xmp_metadata="", name=None):
1194   r"""JPEG-encode an image.
1195 
1196   `image` is a 3-D uint8 Tensor of shape `[height, width, channels]`.
1197 
1198   The attr `format` can be used to override the color format of the encoded
1199   output.  Values can be:
1200 
1201   *   `''`: Use a default format based on the number of channels in the image.
1202   *   `grayscale`: Output a grayscale JPEG image.  The `channels` dimension
1203       of `image` must be 1.
1204   *   `rgb`: Output an RGB JPEG image. The `channels` dimension
1205       of `image` must be 3.
1206 
1207   If `format` is not specified or is the empty string, a default format is picked
1208   in function of the number of channels in `image`:
1209 
1210   *   1: Output a grayscale image.
1211   *   3: Output an RGB image.
1212 
1213   Args:
1214     image: A `Tensor` of type `uint8`.
1215       3-D with shape `[height, width, channels]`.
1216     format: An optional `string` from: `"", "grayscale", "rgb"`. Defaults to `""`.
1217       Per pixel image format.
1218     quality: An optional `int`. Defaults to `95`.
1219       Quality of the compression from 0 to 100 (higher is better and slower).
1220     progressive: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
1221       If True, create a JPEG that loads progressively (coarse to fine).
1222     optimize_size: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
1223       If True, spend CPU/RAM to reduce size with no quality change.
1224     chroma_downsampling: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
1225       See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chroma_subsampling.
1226     density_unit: An optional `string` from: `"in", "cm"`. Defaults to `"in"`.
1227       Unit used to specify `x_density` and `y_density`:
1228       pixels per inch (`'in'`) or centimeter (`'cm'`).
1229     x_density: An optional `int`. Defaults to `300`.
1230       Horizontal pixels per density unit.
1231     y_density: An optional `int`. Defaults to `300`.
1232       Vertical pixels per density unit.

1234       If not empty, embed this XMP metadata in the image header.

1245     if quality is None:
1246       quality = 95
1247     quality = _execute.make_int(quality, "quality")
1248     if progressive is None:
1249       progressive = False
1250     progressive = _execute.make_bool(progressive, "progressive")
1251     if optimize_size is None:
1252       optimize_size = False
1253     optimize_size = _execute.make_bool(optimize_size, "optimize_size")
1254     if chroma_downsampling is None:
1255       chroma_downsampling = True
1256     chroma_downsampling = _execute.make_bool(chroma_downsampling, "chroma_downsampling")
1257     if density_unit is None:
1258       density_unit = "in"
1259     density_unit = _execute.make_str(density_unit, "density_unit")
1260     if x_density is None:
1261       x_density = 300
1262     x_density = _execute.make_int(x_density, "x_density")
1263     if y_density is None:
1264       y_density = 300
1265     y_density = _execute.make_int(y_density, "y_density")
1266     if xmp_metadata is None:

1270         "EncodeJpeg", image=image, format=format, quality=quality,

1440 @tf_export('image.extract_glimpse')
1441 def extract_glimpse(input, size, offsets, centered=True, normalized=True, uniform_noise=True, name=None):
1442   r"""Extracts a glimpse from the input tensor.
1443 
1444   Returns a set of windows called glimpses extracted at location
1445   `offsets` from the input tensor. If the windows only partially
1446   overlaps the inputs, the non overlapping areas will be filled with
1447   random noise.
1448 
1449   The result is a 4-D tensor of shape `[batch_size, glimpse_height,
1450   glimpse_width, channels]`. The channels and batch dimensions are the
1451   same as that of the input tensor. The height and width of the output
1452   windows are specified in the `size` parameter.
1453 
1454   The argument `normalized` and `centered` controls how the windows are built:
1455 
1456   * If the coordinates are normalized but not centered, 0.0 and 1.0
1457     correspond to the minimum and maximum of each height and width
1458     dimension.
1459   * If the coordinates are both normalized and centered, they range from
1460     -1.0 to 1.0. The coordinates (-1.0, -1.0) correspond to the upper
1461     left corner, the lower right corner is located at (1.0, 1.0) and the
1462     center is at (0, 0).
1463   * If the coordinates are not normalized they are interpreted as
1464     numbers of pixels.
1465 
1466   Args:
1467     input: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
1468       A 4-D float tensor of shape `[batch_size, height, width, channels]`.
1469     size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
1470       A 1-D tensor of 2 elements containing the size of the glimpses
1471       to extract.  The glimpse height must be specified first, following
1472       by the glimpse width.

1478       the image, in which case the (0, 0) offset is relative to the center
1479       of the input images. If false, the (0,0) offset corresponds to the
1480       upper left corner of the input images.
1481     normalized: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
1482       indicates if the offset coordinates are normalized.
1483     uniform_noise: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.

1696 def non_max_suppression(boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold=0.5, name=None):
1697   r"""Greedily selects a subset of bounding boxes in descending order of score,
1698 
1699   pruning away boxes that have high intersection-over-union (IOU) overlap
1700   with previously selected boxes.  Bounding boxes are supplied as
1701   [y1, x1, y2, x2], where (y1, x1) and (y2, x2) are the coordinates of any
1702   diagonal pair of box corners and the coordinates can be provided as normalized
1703   (i.e., lying in the interval [0, 1]) or absolute.  Note that this algorithm
1704   is agnostic to where the origin is in the coordinate system.  Note that this
1705   algorithm is invariant to orthogonal transformations and translations
1706   of the coordinate system; thus translating or reflections of the coordinate
1707   system result in the same boxes being selected by the algorithm.
1708   The output of this operation is a set of integers indexing into the input
1709   collection of bounding boxes representing the selected boxes.  The bounding
1710   box coordinates corresponding to the selected indices can then be obtained
1711   using the `tf.gather operation`.  For example:
1712     selected_indices = tf.image.non_max_suppression(
1713         boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold)
1714     selected_boxes = tf.gather(boxes, selected_indices)
1715 
1716   Args:
1717     boxes: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
1718       A 2-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes, 4]`.
1719     scores: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
1720       A 1-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` representing a single
1721       score corresponding to each box (each row of boxes).
1722     max_output_size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
1723       A scalar integer tensor representing the maximum number of
1724       boxes to be selected by non max suppression.
1725     iou_threshold: An optional `float`. Defaults to `0.5`.
1726       A float representing the threshold for deciding whether boxes
1727       overlap too much with respect to IOU.
1728     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1729 
1730   Returns:
1731     A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
1732   """
1733   _ctx = _context._context
1734   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1735     if iou_threshold is None:
1736       iou_threshold = 0.5
1737     iou_threshold = _execute.make_float(iou_threshold, "iou_threshold")
1738     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1739         "NonMaxSuppression", boxes=boxes, scores=scores,
1740         max_output_size=max_output_size, iou_threshold=iou_threshold,
1741         name=name)
1742     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1743     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1744     _attrs = ("iou_threshold", _op.get_attr("iou_threshold"))
1745     _execute.record_gradient(
1746       "NonMaxSuppression", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1747     _result, = _result
1748     return _result
1749 
1750   else:
1751     try:
1752       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1753         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1754         "NonMaxSuppression", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, boxes,
1755         scores, max_output_size, "iou_threshold", iou_threshold)
1756       return _result
1757     except _core._FallbackException:
1758       return non_max_suppression_eager_fallback(
1759           boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold=iou_threshold,
1760           name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1761     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1762       if name is not None:
1763         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1764       else:
1765         message = e.message
1766       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
1767

1880 def non_max_suppression_v3(boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold, name=None):
1881   r"""Greedily selects a subset of bounding boxes in descending order of score,
1882 
1883   pruning away boxes that have high intersection-over-union (IOU) overlap
1884   with previously selected boxes.  Bounding boxes with score less than
1885   `score_threshold` are removed.  Bounding boxes are supplied as
1886   [y1, x1, y2, x2], where (y1, x1) and (y2, x2) are the coordinates of any
1887   diagonal pair of box corners and the coordinates can be provided as normalized
1888   (i.e., lying in the interval [0, 1]) or absolute.  Note that this algorithm
1889   is agnostic to where the origin is in the coordinate system and more
1890   generally is invariant to orthogonal transformations and translations
1891   of the coordinate system; thus translating or reflections of the coordinate
1892   system result in the same boxes being selected by the algorithm.
1893   The output of this operation is a set of integers indexing into the input
1894   collection of bounding boxes representing the selected boxes.  The bounding
1895   box coordinates corresponding to the selected indices can then be obtained
1896   using the `tf.gather operation`.  For example:
1897     selected_indices = tf.image.non_max_suppression_v2(
1898         boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold)
1899     selected_boxes = tf.gather(boxes, selected_indices)
1900 
1901   Args:
1902     boxes: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `half`, `float32`.
1903       A 2-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes, 4]`.
1904     scores: A `Tensor`. Must have the same type as `boxes`.
1905       A 1-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` representing a single
1906       score corresponding to each box (each row of boxes).
1907     max_output_size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
1908       A scalar integer tensor representing the maximum number of
1909       boxes to be selected by non max suppression.
1910     iou_threshold: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
1911       A 0-D float tensor representing the threshold for deciding whether
1912       boxes overlap too much with respect to IOU.
1913     score_threshold: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
1914       A 0-D float tensor representing the threshold for deciding when to remove
1915       boxes based on score.
1916     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1917 
1918   Returns:
1919     A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
1920   """
1921   _ctx = _context._context
1922   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1923     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1924         "NonMaxSuppressionV3", boxes=boxes, scores=scores,
1925         max_output_size=max_output_size, iou_threshold=iou_threshold,
1926         score_threshold=score_threshold, name=name)
1927     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1928     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1929     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"))
1930     _execute.record_gradient(
1931       "NonMaxSuppressionV3", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1932     _result, = _result
1933     return _result
1934 
1935   else:
1936     try:
1937       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1938         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1939         "NonMaxSuppressionV3", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, boxes,
1940         scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold)
1941       return _result
1942     except _core._FallbackException:
1943       return non_max_suppression_v3_eager_fallback(
1944           boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold,
1945           name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1946     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1947       if name is not None:
1948         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1949       else:
1950         message = e.message
1951       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

1979 def non_max_suppression_v4(boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold, pad_to_max_output_size=False, name=None):
1980   r"""Greedily selects a subset of bounding boxes in descending order of score,
1981 
1982   pruning away boxes that have high intersection-over-union (IOU) overlap
1983   with previously selected boxes.  Bounding boxes with score less than
1984   `score_threshold` are removed.  Bounding boxes are supplied as
1985   [y1, x1, y2, x2], where (y1, x1) and (y2, x2) are the coordinates of any
1986   diagonal pair of box corners and the coordinates can be provided as normalized
1987   (i.e., lying in the interval [0, 1]) or absolute.  Note that this algorithm
1988   is agnostic to where the origin is in the coordinate system and more
1989   generally is invariant to orthogonal transformations and translations
1990   of the coordinate system; thus translating or reflections of the coordinate
1991   system result in the same boxes being selected by the algorithm.
1992   The output of this operation is a set of integers indexing into the input
1993   collection of bounding boxes representing the selected boxes.  The bounding
1994   box coordinates corresponding to the selected indices can then be obtained
1995   using the `tf.gather operation`.  For example:
1996     selected_indices = tf.image.non_max_suppression_v2(
1997         boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold)
1998     selected_boxes = tf.gather(boxes, selected_indices)
1999 
2000   Args:
2001     boxes: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `half`, `float32`.
2002       A 2-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes, 4]`.
2003     scores: A `Tensor`. Must have the same type as `boxes`.
2004       A 1-D float tensor of shape `[num_boxes]` representing a single
2005       score corresponding to each box (each row of boxes).
2006     max_output_size: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
2007       A scalar integer tensor representing the maximum number of
2008       boxes to be selected by non max suppression.
2009     iou_threshold: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
2010       A 0-D float tensor representing the threshold for deciding whether
2011       boxes overlap too much with respect to IOU.
2012     score_threshold: A `Tensor` of type `float32`.
2013       A 0-D float tensor representing the threshold for deciding when to remove
2014       boxes based on score.
2015     pad_to_max_output_size: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
2016       If true, the output `selected_indices` is padded to be of length
2017       `max_output_size`. Defaults to false.
2018     name: A name for the operation (optional).
2019 
2020   Returns:
2021     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (selected_indices, valid_outputs).
2022 
2023     selected_indices: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
2024     valid_outputs: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
2025   """
2026   _ctx = _context._context
2027   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
2028     if pad_to_max_output_size is None:
2029       pad_to_max_output_size = False
2030     pad_to_max_output_size = _execute.make_bool(pad_to_max_output_size, "pad_to_max_output_size")
2031     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
2032         "NonMaxSuppressionV4", boxes=boxes, scores=scores,
2033         max_output_size=max_output_size, iou_threshold=iou_threshold,
2034         score_threshold=score_threshold,
2035         pad_to_max_output_size=pad_to_max_output_size, name=name)
2036     _result = _op.outputs[:]
2037     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
2038     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"), "pad_to_max_output_size",
2039               _op.get_attr("pad_to_max_output_size"))
2040     _execute.record_gradient(
2041       "NonMaxSuppressionV4", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
2042     _result = _NonMaxSuppressionV4Output._make(_result)
2043     return _result
2044 
2045   else:
2046     try:
2047       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
2048         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
2049         "NonMaxSuppressionV4", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, boxes,
2050         scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold,
2051         "pad_to_max_output_size", pad_to_max_output_size)
2052       _result = _NonMaxSuppressionV4Output._make(_result)
2053       return _result
2054     except _core._FallbackException:
2055       return non_max_suppression_v4_eager_fallback(
2056           boxes, scores, max_output_size, iou_threshold, score_threshold,
2057           pad_to_max_output_size=pad_to_max_output_size, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
2058     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:

2423 @tf_export('image.resize_area')
2424 def resize_area(images, size, align_corners=False, name=None):
2425   r"""Resize `images` to `size` using area interpolation.
2426 
2427   Input images can be of different types but output images are always float.
2428 
2429   The range of pixel values for the output image might be slightly different
2430   from the range for the input image because of limited numerical precision.
2431   To guarantee an output range, for example `[0.0, 1.0]`, apply
2432   `tf.clip_by_value` to the output.
2433 
2434   Each output pixel is computed by first transforming the pixel's footprint into
2435   the input tensor and then averaging the pixels that intersect the footprint. An
2436   input pixel's contribution to the average is weighted by the fraction of its
2437   area that intersects the footprint.  This is the same as OpenCV's INTER_AREA.
2438 
2439   Args:
2440     images: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `int8`, `uint8`, `int16`, `uint16`, `int32`, `int64`, `half`, `float32`, `float64`.
2441       4-D with shape `[batch, height, width, channels]`.

2950 def sample_distorted_bounding_box(image_size, bounding_boxes, seed=0, seed2=0, min_object_covered=0.1, aspect_ratio_range=[0.75, 1.33], area_range=[0.05, 1], max_attempts=100, use_image_if_no_bounding_boxes=False, name=None):
2951   r"""Generate a single randomly distorted bounding box for an image.
2952 
2953   Bounding box annotations are often supplied in addition to ground-truth labels
2954   in image recognition or object localization tasks. A common technique for
2955   training such a system is to randomly distort an image while preserving
2956   its content, i.e. *data augmentation*. This Op outputs a randomly distorted
2957   localization of an object, i.e. bounding box, given an `image_size`,
2958   `bounding_boxes` and a series of constraints.
2959 
2960   The output of this Op is a single bounding box that may be used to crop the
2961   original image. The output is returned as 3 tensors: `begin`, `size` and
2962   `bboxes`. The first 2 tensors can be fed directly into `tf.slice` to crop the
2963   image. The latter may be supplied to `tf.image.draw_bounding_boxes` to visualize
2964   what the bounding box looks like.
2965 
2966   Bounding boxes are supplied and returned as `[y_min, x_min, y_max, x_max]`. The
2967   bounding box coordinates are floats in `[0.0, 1.0]` relative to the width and
2968   height of the underlying image.
2969 
2970   For example,
2971 
2972   ```python
2973       # Generate a single distorted bounding box.
2974       begin, size, bbox_for_draw = tf.image.sample_distorted_bounding_box(
2975           tf.shape(image),
2976           bounding_boxes=bounding_boxes)
2977 
2978       # Draw the bounding box in an image summary.
2979       image_with_box = tf.image.draw_bounding_boxes(tf.expand_dims(image, 0),
2980                                                     bbox_for_draw)
2981       tf.summary.image('images_with_box', image_with_box)
2982 
2983       # Employ the bounding box to distort the image.
2984       distorted_image = tf.slice(image, begin, size)
2985   ```
2986 
2987   Note that if no bounding box information is available, setting
2988   `use_image_if_no_bounding_boxes = true` will assume there is a single implicit
2989   bounding box covering the whole image. If `use_image_if_no_bounding_boxes` is
2990   false and no bounding boxes are supplied, an error is raised.

2999       If either `seed` or `seed2` are set to non-zero, the random number
3000       generator is seeded by the given `seed`.  Otherwise, it is seeded by a random
3001       seed.

3006       fraction of any bounding box supplied. The value of this parameter should be
3007       non-negative. In the case of 0, the cropped area does not need to overlap
3008       any of the bounding boxes supplied.
3009     aspect_ratio_range: An optional list of `floats`. Defaults to `[0.75, 1.33]`.
3010       The cropped area of the image must have an aspect ratio =
3011       width / height within this range.
3012     area_range: An optional list of `floats`. Defaults to `[0.05, 1]`.
3013       The cropped area of the image must contain a fraction of the
3014       supplied image within this range.
3015     max_attempts: An optional `int`. Defaults to `100`.
3016       Number of attempts at generating a cropped region of the image
3017       of the specified constraints. After `max_attempts` failures, return the entire
3018       image.
3019     use_image_if_no_bounding_boxes: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
3020       Controls behavior if no bounding boxes supplied.
3021       If true, assume an implicit bounding box covering the whole input. If false,
3022       raise an error.
3023     name: A name for the operation (optional).

3029     size: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `image_size`.
